sql:
SELECT location_type, SUM(population_size) AS total_population
FROM census_locations
GROUP BY location_type;

SELECT location_name, population_size 
FROM census_locations 
WHERE census_location_id = 0;

SELECT DISTINCT column_name 
FROM census_data 
WHERE census_location_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_locations
FROM census_locations
WHERE population_size > 0;

external_knowledge:
A population size of over a million refers to a metropolitan area with a large population; 
"States in the US" refers to the 50 states that make up the United States of America; 
"Contact email ending with '@us.gov'" indicates that the email address is affiliated with the US government.

